OL,7,F"It definitely makes you feel good
OL,8,Fleaving because you go away and you're
OL,9,Fthinking about the fact that could be
OL,10,Fso beneficial to somebody."
OL,12,FSome of the most common circumstances
OL,13,Fwhere a blood transfusion might be
OL,14,Fneeded are for patients who have been
OL,15,Finvolved in an accident or for mothers
OL,16,Fduring childbirth.
OL,18,FThe service is currently developing a
OL,19,Fway to notify donors when their blood
OL,20,Fhas been sent to a hospital for use.
